---

Toast the rice: Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp} in a #medium pot{} over medium-high heat. Add half the @Basmati rice{1.5%cup} and stir continuously until rice is golden brown.

Cook the rice: Add the remaining rice and @water{3%cups} to the #pot. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer for about ~{15%minutes}, until tender.

Prep the ingredients: Core, seed, and remove the white ribs from the @red bell pepper{2} then thinly slice. Mince or grate the @garlic{4%cloves}. Thinly slice the @scallions{4}, keeping the greens and whites separate. Cut the @lime{1} into wedges. Chop the @shrimp{20%oz} into 1/2-inch pieces.

Cook the veg and shrimp: Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add the bell pepper, scallion whites, and @chili flakes{1%tsp}(to taste) to the pan and cook, tossing, ~{5-7%minutes}, until tender. Add the shrimp to the pan and cook, tossing, for ~{1-2%minutes}, until cooked through. Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Fluff the rice with a fork and add to the pan along with the @corn{12%oz}, scallion greens, and @soy sauce{12%tsp}. Cook, tossing, for ~{1%minute}. Season with salt and pepper.

Serve with a wedge of lime and enjoy!